Build paraphrase dataset¶

In [ ]:
class ParaphraseDataset(Dataset):
    def __init__(self, tokenizer, data, max_len=256):

        self.data = data
        self.source_column = "sentence1"
        self.target_column = "sentence2"

        self.max_len = max_len
        self.tokenizer = tokenizer
        self.inputs = []
        self.targets = []

        self._build()

    def __len__(self):
        return len(self.inputs)

    def __getitem__(self, index):
        src = self.inputs[index]["input_ids"].squeeze()
        target = self.targets[index]["input_ids"].squeeze()

        src_mask = self.inputs[index]["attention_mask"].squeeze() 
        target_mask = self.targets[index]["attention_mask"].squeeze() 

        return {"source_ids": src, "source_mask": src_mask, "target_ids": target, "target_mask": target_mask}

    def _build(self):
        for idx in range(len(self.data)):
            input_data, target = self.data.loc[idx, self.source_column], self.data.loc[idx, self.target_column]

            input_data = "paraphrase: "+ input_data + ' </s>'
            target = target + " </s>"

            # tokenize inputs
            tokenized_inputs = self.tokenizer.batch_encode_plus(
                [input_data], max_length=self.max_len, pad_to_max_length=True, return_tensors="pt", truncation='longest_first'
            )
            # tokenize targets
            tokenized_targets = self.tokenizer.batch_encode_plus(
                [target], max_length=self.max_len, pad_to_max_length=True, return_tensors="pt", truncation='longest_first'
            )

            self.inputs.append(tokenized_inputs)
            self.targets.append(tokenized_targets)

T5FineTuner¶

In [ ]:
class T5FineTuner(pl.LightningModule):
    def __init__(self, args):
        super(T5FineTuner, self).__init__()
        self.args = args

        self.model = T5ForConditionalGeneration.from_pretrained(args.model_name)
        self.tokenizer = T5Tokenizer.from_pretrained(args.model_name)

        self.training_stats=[]

    def is_logger(self):  #Lightning supports the most popular logging frameworks.TensorBoard is used by default
        return True

    def forward(
            self, input_ids, attention_mask=None, decoder_input_ids=None, decoder_attention_mask=None, lm_labels=None
    ):
        return self.model(
            input_ids,
            attention_mask=attention_mask,
            decoder_input_ids=decoder_input_ids,
            decoder_attention_mask=decoder_attention_mask,
            lm_labels=lm_labels,
        )

    def _step(self, batch):
        lm_labels = batch["target_ids"]
        lm_labels[lm_labels[:, :] == self.tokenizer.pad_token_id] = -100

        outputs = self(
            input_ids=batch["source_ids"],
            attention_mask=batch["source_mask"],
            lm_labels=lm_labels,
            decoder_attention_mask=batch['target_mask'] 
          )

        loss = outputs[0]

        return loss

    def training_step(self, batch, batch_idx):
        loss = self._step(batch)
        tensorboard_logs = {"train_loss": loss}
        return {"loss": loss, "log": tensorboard_logs}

    def training_epoch_end(self, outputs):
        avg_train_loss = torch.stack([x["loss"] for x in outputs]).mean()
        train_ppl = math.exp(avg_train_loss)
        tensorboard_logs = {"avg_train_loss": avg_train_loss}
        self.training_stats.append ({"avg_train_loss": avg_train_loss, "train_perplexity": train_ppl})
        return {"avg_train_loss": avg_train_loss, "log": tensorboard_logs, 'progress_bar': tensorboard_logs}

    def validation_step(self, batch, batch_idx):
        loss = self._step(batch)
        return  {"val_loss": loss}

    def validation_epoch_end(self, outputs):
        avg_loss = torch.stack([x["val_loss"] for x in outputs]).mean()
        val_ppl = math.exp(avg_loss)
        tensorboard_logs = {"val_loss": avg_loss}
        self.training_stats.append({"avg_val_loss": avg_loss,"validation_perplexity":val_ppl})
        return  {"avg_val_loss": avg_loss, "log": tensorboard_logs, 'progress_bar': tensorboard_logs}

    def configure_optimizers(self):
        model = self.model
        no_decay = ["bias", "LayerNorm.weight"] # decouple bias and LayerNorm.weight with weight decay for better performance with AdamW
        optimizer_grouped_parameters = [
            {
                "params": [p for n, p in model.named_parameters() if not any(nd in n for nd in no_decay)],
                "weight_decay": self.args.weight_decay,
            },
            {
                "params": [p for n, p in model.named_parameters() if any(nd in n for nd in no_decay)],
                "weight_decay": 0.0,
            },
        ]
        optimizer = AdamW(optimizer_grouped_parameters, lr=self.args.learning_rate, eps=self.args.adam_epsilon)
        self.opt = optimizer
        return [optimizer]

    def optimizer_step(self, epoch, batch_idx, optimizer, optimizer_idx, second_order_closure=None, on_tpu=False, using_native_amp=False, using_lbfgs=False):
        optimizer.step()
        optimizer.zero_grad()
        self.lr_scheduler.step()

    def train_dataloader(self):
        train_dataset = ParaphraseDataset(tokenizer=self.tokenizer, data=self.args.train_datasource, max_len=self.args.max_seq_length)
        train_dataloader = DataLoader(train_dataset, batch_size=self.args.batch_size, drop_last=True, shuffle=True,
                                num_workers=4)
        total_steps = (
                (len(train_dataloader.dataset) // (self.args.batch_size))
                // self.args.gradient_accumulation_steps * float(self.args.num_train_epochs) 
        )
        
        scheduler = get_linear_schedule_with_warmup(
            self.opt, num_warmup_steps=self.args.warmup_steps, num_training_steps=total_steps
        )
        self.lr_scheduler = scheduler
        return train_dataloader

    def val_dataloader(self):
        val_dataset = ParaphraseDataset(tokenizer=self.tokenizer, data=self.args.val_datasource, max_len=self.args.max_seq_length) 
        return DataLoader(val_dataset, batch_size=self.args.batch_size, num_workers=4)

all_stats =[ ]

lr_list = [5e-8, 5e-6, 5e-4]
eps_list = [1e-8, 1e-6]

train_params = dict(
    accumulate_grad_batches=args.gradient_accumulation_steps,
    gpus=args.n_gpu,
    max_epochs=args.num_train_epochs,
    amp_level=args.opt_level,
    gradient_clip_val=args.max_grad_norm,

)


n= 1
for lr in lr_list:
    for eps in eps_list:
        args_dict.update(
        { 
            'learning_rate':lr,'adam_epsilon':eps, 
            'train_datasource': data_train_tune, 'val_datasource': data_dev_tune,
            'output_dir': 't5_paraphrase', 'num_train_epochs':2,
            'max_seq_length':512, 'batch_size': 8
                  }
                 )
        args = argparse.Namespace(**args_dict)

        # print (args_dict)

        print ("Initialize model")
        model = T5FineTuner(args)
     
        trainer = pl.Trainer(**train_params)

        print (" Training model")
        trainer.fit(model)

        print ("Training", str(n), "finished")

        n+=1

        all_stats.append(model.training_stats)

        print ("Training statistics saved")

def generate_sent(sentence):
    text =  "paraphrase: " + sentence + " </s>"
    # print(text)
    max_len = 128
    encoding = tokenizer.encode_plus(text,pad_to_max_length=True, return_tensors="pt")
    input_ids, attention_masks = encoding["input_ids"].to(device), encoding["attention_mask"].to(device)

    outputs = model_tuned.generate(
        input_ids=input_ids, attention_mask=attention_masks,
        do_sample=True,
        max_length=300,
        top_k=100,
        top_p=0.95,
        early_stopping=True,
        repetition_penalty=3,
        num_return_sequences=3
    )

    final_outputs =[]
    for output in outputs:
        sent = tokenizer.decode(output, skip_special_tokens=True,clean_up_tokenization_spaces=True)
        if sent.lower() != sentence.lower() and sent not in final_outputs:
            final_outputs.append(sent)
    # for n, final_output in enumerate(final_outputs):
      # print(str(n+1)+": "+ final_output)
    
    return final_outputs

import time
import datetime
def format_time(elapsed):
    return str(datetime.timedelta(seconds=int(round((elapsed)))))
    



    













In [ ]:



    


def train(model, args):
    no_decay = ["bias", "LayerNorm.weight"]
    optimizer_grouped_parameters = [
          {
              "params": [p for n, p in model.named_parameters() if not any(nd in n for nd in no_decay)],
              "weight_decay": args.weight_decay,
          },
          {
              "params": [p for n, p in model.named_parameters() if any(nd in n for nd in no_decay)],
              "weight_decay": 0.0,
          },
      ]

    optimizer = AdamW(model.parameters(), lr=args.learning_rate, eps= args.adam_epsilon)
    training_steps = (
                  (len(train_dataloader) // (args.train_batch_size))
                  // args.gradient_accumulation_steps
                  * float(args.num_train_epochs)
                  )
    
    scheduler = get_linear_schedule_with_warmup(optimizer, num_warmup_steps=args.warmup_steps, num_training_steps=training_steps)

    total_t0 = time.time()
    training_stats = []

    for epoch_i in tqdm(range(0,args.num_train_epochs)):

       #============================== training ================================#

        print('======== Epoch {:} / {:} ========'.format(epoch_i + 1, args.num_train_epochs))
        print('Training...')

        t0 = time.time()
        total_train_loss = 0
        
        for step, batch in tqdm(enumerate(train_dataloader)):

          lm_labels = batch["target_ids"].to(device)
          # decoder_input_ids = lm_labels[:, :-1].contiguous() ###
          
          lm_labels[lm_labels[:, :] == tokenizer.pad_token_id] = -100
          
          input_ids=batch["source_ids"].to(device)
          attention_mask=batch["source_mask"].to(device)
          decoder_attention_mask=batch['target_mask'].to(device)

          model.zero_grad()
        
          outputs = model(
              input_ids,
              attention_mask=attention_mask,
              decoder_input_ids=None,
              decoder_attention_mask=decoder_attention_mask,
              lm_labels=lm_labels
            )
          
          loss = outputs[0]  

          batch_loss = loss.item()
          total_train_loss += batch_loss

          # optimizer.zero_grad()
          loss.backward()
          optimizer.step()
          scheduler.step()
      # calculate average train loss and perplexity
        avg_train_loss = total_train_loss / len(train_dataloader)   
        train_ppl = math.exp(avg_train_loss)
        training_time = format_time(time.time() - t0)

        print("  Average training loss: {0:.2f}".format(avg_train_loss))
        print("  Training perplexity: {0:.2f}".format(train_ppl))
        print("  Training epoch took: {:}".format(training_time))
      

    #====================== validation ================================#
        print("")
        print('======== Epoch {:} / {:} ========'.format(epoch_i + 1, args.num_train_epochs))
        print('Validating...')

        t0 = time.time()
        model.eval()
        total_eval_loss=0

        with torch.no_grad(): 
            for batch in tqdm (val_dataloader):
                lm_labels = batch["target_ids"].to(device)
                lm_labels[lm_labels[:, :] == tokenizer.pad_token_id] = -100
                input_ids=batch["source_ids"].to(device)
                attention_mask=batch["source_mask"].to(device)
                decoder_attention_mask=batch['target_mask'].to(device)

                outputs = model(
                                input_ids,
                                attention_mask=attention_mask,
                                decoder_input_ids=None,
                                decoder_attention_mask=decoder_attention_mask,
                                lm_labels=lm_labels
                              )

                loss = outputs[0]  

                batch_loss = loss.item()
                total_eval_loss += batch_loss        

            avg_val_loss = total_eval_loss / len(val_dataloader)
            val_ppl = math.exp(avg_val_loss)
            validation_time = format_time(time.time() - t0)    

        print("  Validation Loss: {0:.2f}".format(avg_val_loss))
        print("  Validation perplexity: {0:.2f}".format(val_ppl))
        print("  Validation took: {:}".format(validation_time))

        # Record all statistics from this epoch.
        training_stats.append(
            {
                'epoch': epoch_i + 1,
                'Training Loss': avg_train_loss,
                'Valid. Loss': avg_val_loss,
                'Training ppl': train_ppl,
                'Validation ppl': val_ppl,
                'Training Time': training_time,
                'Validation Time': validation_time
            }
        )

        print("")
        print("Training complete!")
        print("Total training took {:} (h:mm:ss)".format(format_time(time.time()-total_t0)))
    return model, training_stats
